<h2 class="pen"><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=998" title="Permanent link to this article">Darlene&#8217;s take</a></h2>

<div class="post">

<div class="entrytext">

	<p>Still trying to accept the election results. I can not believe our country has made such a colossal mistake.  We will all pay for it.  Mark my words.</p>

	<p>On the good side, the Republicans are going to have to clean up their own messes both here and abroad.  Kerry will not be blamed for not being able to fix everything Bush screwed up within 4 years.  The bad news is that he has 4 years to make it worse.</p>

	<p>While I still question the validity of the election (no paper backup on many machines in Ohio and Florida so why even consider a recount, a machine in Ohio that tallied an extra 4000 or so votes &#8211; all for Bush, and both state&#8217;s exit polls showing an entirely different story than the ballots). Kerry was correct in that there were not enough provisional ballots to change the result.  It seems that the gay rights issues, abortion, and just plain fear brought out many of the Republican voters. How the soaring deficit, struggling economy, jobs going overseas, environmental issues, not to mention the nightmare in Iraq can be ignored is beyond me.</p>

	<p>So what do we do now?  We need to pay attention these next four years and hold this administration accountable.  Be as informed as possible. Read the news, instead of just getting 30 second sound bites on the television.  We have a great resource of national and international newspapers on the internet.</p>

	<p>I am sorry for the kids as well. It was a very close race and they can be proud that our candidate did so well against so much misinformation.  Our country made a mistake.  It happens, and we must do everything we can to make sure it does not happen again.</p>

	<p>I believe Kerry would have been a president who united our nation.  I am sorry we will not have the benefit of his wisdom, experience and patriotism.</p>

	<p>I am praying for all of our futures,<br />
Darlene</p>



 

<p class="postmetadata alt">

